com.anthem.selenium.utils

Class XMLJSONUtils

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.anthem.selenium.utils.XMLJSONUtils

  • public class XMLJSONUtils
extends Object
    This class provides the methods for handling JSON and XML Objects. This Utility class provides methods for retrieving/updating data in XML or JSON. This does not support . in key.
    Author:
    shiva.katula

      • getObjectValue

        public static Object getObjectValue(String jsonString,
                                    String elementToRetrieve)
        This method returns JSON Object of the element from JSON String. 
         This method uses json Path Expressions (Avoid using "$.")
 eg:- eligibility[1].mbuCd.name - For Array based retrievals
 eg:- eligibility - For Object based retrievals of entire list of Array
 eg:- genderCd  - Free Node retrievals
 eg:- ".eligibility[?(@.name==Shiva)]" - For getting a Node with attribute "name" and value "Shiva" from all eligibility nodes.
        Parameters:
        jsonString - jsonString
        elementToRetrieve - query for element from jsonString
        Returns:
        String

        public static String getStringValue(String jsonString,
                                    String elementToRetrieve)
        This method returns JSON String of the element from Response. 
         This method uses json Path Expressions (Avoid using "$.")
 eg:- eligibility[1].mbuCd.name - For Array based retrievals
 eg:- genderCd  - Free Node retrievals
 If we have spaces in key then ['key name']
        Parameters:
        jsonString - jsonString to query
        elementToRetrieve - query for element from json String
        Returns:
        String

      • getJSONArray

        public static org.json.JSONArray getJSONArray(String jsonString,
                                              String elementToRetrieve)
        This method returns JSON Array of the element from JSON String. Make sure the element to retrieve is an array/collection of elements. 
         This method uses json Path Expressions (Avoid using "$.")
 eg:- member.elgibilities - For Array based retrievals of eligibility objects
        Parameters:
        jsonString - jsonString
        elementToRetrieve - query for element from jsonString
        Returns:
        String

      • addJSONEntry

        public static boolean addJSONEntry(File jsonFile,
                                   String key,
                                   String value)
        This method add an entry (Key = Value) in the json file. 
         Usage :- 
 For adding an element to sub node/element in json, provide hierarchy "eligibility.subscriber.name"
 For adding and element to root, provide simple key
        Parameters:
        jsonFile - File (json format only)
        key - key to search for which value will be replaced
        value - value to set for the key
        Returns:
        boolean

      • updateOrAddJSONEntry

        public static boolean updateOrAddJSONEntry(File jsonFile,
                                           String key,
                                           String newValue)
        This method updates the value of existing key with new value in the json file. If the key is not found then it creates and new entry (key = value) to the root of json file.
        Parameters:
        jsonFile - File (json format only)
        key - key to search for which value will be replaced
        newValue - new value to replace existing value of key
        Returns:
        boolean Added or Updated successfully
